tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The results indicate mild arterial acidemia (low arterial pH) with low oxygen saturation, suggesting possible respiratory compromise or hypoxemia. Venous pCO₂ is slightly elevated, which may reflect hypoventilation or impaired gas exchange. Activated clotting time is mildly decreased. Other parameters are within normal limits. Clinical correlation and further evaluation of respiratory and coagulation status are recommended.
